Namibian Police Seize 2,000 Polished Diamonds From Plant, Namibian Reports

-- B y   C h a m w e   K a i r a
-- 
2011-07-20T08:16:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/namibian-police-seize-2-000-polished-diamonds-from-plant-namibian-reports.html
Namibian police seized 2,000
polished gems from a factory belonging to Lev Leviev Diamonds in
January, the  Namibian reported , citing Managing Director
Kombadayetu Kapwanga.  The diamonds have a total weight of about 1,000 carats, the
Windhoek-based newspaper said, citing unidentified people. A
former LLD employee from  Israel  fled the country following the
police raid, the Namibian said, citing Kapwanga.  A carat is a fifth of a gram.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chamwe Kaira in Windhoek at 
 ckaira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin on  at  asguazzin@bloomberg.net  